{"title_page": "Walebing Important Bird Area", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2019}}\n[[File:Calyptorhynchus latirostris Carnaby gnangarra.jpg|thumb|right|250px|alt=Pair of short-billed black cockatoos; one perched in a tree, the other flying towards it|The site is important for short-billed black cockatoos]]\n\nThe '''Walebing Important Bird Area''' comprises a 13&nbsp;km<sup>2</sup> tract of land in the vicinity of the rural township of [[Walebing, Western Australia|Walebing]], in the northern [[Wheatbelt (Western Australia)|wheatbelt region]] of south-west [[Western Australia]].\n\n==Description==\nThe [[Important Bird Area]] (IBA) contains nesting trees suitable for [[Calyptorhynchus|black cockatoos]] on two private properties. It is defined by several fragments of remnant native vegetation, including small clusters and isolated large trees, but excludes areas of pasture, crops and non-native plants.  It has a [[Mediterranean climate]].<ref>BirdLife International. (2011). Important Bird Areas factsheet: Walebing. Downloaded from http://www.birdlife.org on 2011-11-19.</ref>\n\n==Birds==\nThe site has been identified as an IBA by [[BirdLife International]] because it supports up to 40 breeding pairs of endangered [[short-billed black cockatoo]]s which nest in woodland remnants and isolated trees and feed in native [[shrubland]]s. It also supports [[western corella]]s, [[regent parrot]]s, [[rufous treecreeper]]s and [[blue-breasted fairywren]]s.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.birdata.com.au/iba.vm |title=IBA: Walebing |accessdate=2011-11-19 |work= Birdata |first= |last= |publisher=Birds Australia |date= }}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{coord|30|41|37|S|116|15|29|E|display=title|region:AU-WA_type:landmark}}\n\n[[Category:Wheatbelt (Western Australia)]]\n[[Category:Important Bird Areas of Western Australia]]\n\n\n{{WesternAustralia-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2019}}\n[[File:Calyptorhynchus latirostris Carnaby gnangarra.jpg|thumb|right|250px|alt=Pair of short-billed black cockatoos; one perched in a tree, the other flying towards it|The site is important for short-billed black cockatoos]]\n\nThe '''Walebing Important Bird Area''' comprises a 13&nbsp;km<sup>2</sup> tract of land in the vicinity of the rural township of [[Walebing, Western Australia|Walebing]], in the northern [[Wheatbelt (Western Australia)|whatbelt region]] of south-west [[Western Australia]].\n\n==Description==\nThe [[Important Bird Area]] (IBA) contains nesting trees suitable for [[Calyptorhynchus|black cockatoos]] on two private properties. It is defined by several fragments of remnant native vegetation, including small clusters and isolated large trees, but excludes areas of pasture, crops and non-native plants.  It has a [[Mediterranean climate]].<ref>BirdLife International. (2011). Important Bird Areas factsheet: Walebing. Downloaded from http://www.birdlife.org on 2011-11-19.</ref>\n\n==Birds==\nThe site has been identified as an IBA by [[BirdLife International]] because it supports up to 40 breeding pairs of endangered [[short-billed black cockatoo]]s which nest in woodland remnants and isolated trees and feed in native [[shrubland]]s. It also supports [[western corella]]s, [[regent parrot]]s, [[rufous treecreeper]]s and [[blue-breasted fairywren]]s.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.birdata.com.au/iba.vm |title=IBA: Walebing |accessdate=2011-11-19 |work= Birdata |first= |last= |publisher=Birds Australia |date= }}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{coord|30|41|37|S|116|15|29|E|display=title|region:AU-WA_type:landmark}}\n\n[[Category:Wheatbelt (Western Australia)]]\n[[Category:Important Bird Areas of Western Australia]]\n\n\n{{WesternAustralia-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Skaldis", "label": "safe", "comment": "typo", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Walebing_Important_Bird_Area"}
{"title_page": "Salva Ferrer", "text_new": "{{short description|Spanish footballer}}\n{{Spanish name|Ferrer|Canals}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Salva Ferrer\n| image = \n| caption = Salva Ferrer in 2018\n| full_name = Salvador Ferrer Canals\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1998|1|21|df=y}}\n| birth_place = Sant Joan Samora, Spain\n| height = 1.84 m\n| position = [[Defender (association football)#Centre-back|Centre back]]\n| currentclub = [[Spezia Calcio|Spezia]]\n| clubnumber = 21\n| youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = [[RCD Espanyol|Espanyol]]\n| youthyears2 = | youthclubs2 = J\u00e0bac Terrassa\n| youthyears3 = | youthclubs3 = Martorell\n| youthyears4 = 2016\u20132017 | youthclubs4 = [[CF Damm|Damm]]\n| years1 = 2015\u20132016 | clubs1 = Martorell | caps1 = | goals1 = \n| years2 = 2017\u20132018 | clubs2 = [[CF Pobla de Mafumet|Pobla Mafumet]] | caps2 = 41 | goals2 = 2\n| years3 = 2018\u20132019 | clubs3 = [[Gimn\u00e0stic de Tarragona|Gimn\u00e0stic]] | caps3 = 21 | goals3 = 0\n| years4 = 2019\u2013 | clubs4 = [[Spezia Calcio|Spezia]] | caps4 = 0 | goals4 = 0\n| nationalyears1 = | nationalteam1 = | nationalcaps1 = | nationalgoals1 = \n| club-update = 9 June 2019\n| nationalteam-update = \n}}\n\n'''Salvador''' \"'''Salva'''\" '''Ferrer Canals''' (born 21 January 1998) is a Spanish professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays for Italian club [[Spezia Calcio]] as a [[Defender (association football)#Centre-back|central defender]].\n\n==Club career==\nBorn in Sant Joan Samora, [[Province of Barcelona|Barcelona]], [[Catalonia]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gimnasticdetarragona.cat/jugador/salva|title=Salva|publisher=Gimn\u00e0stic Tarragona|language=ca|accessdate=11 June 2019}}</ref> Ferrer represented [[RCD Espanyol]], UFB J\u00e0bac Terrassa, CF Martorell \u2013 where he made his senior debut in ''Tercera Catalana''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://cfmartorell.cat/2018/08/27/la-perla-salva-ferrer-recorda-el-seu-passat-al-cf-martorell/|title='La perla' Salva Ferrer recorda el seu passat al CF Martorell|trans-title='The pearl' Salva Ferrer remembers his past at CF Martorell|publisher=CF Martorell|language=ca|date=27 August 2018|access-date=8 October 2018}}</ref> \u2013 and [[CF Damm]] as a youth.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.regio7.cat/esports/2018/08/27/preparat-jugar-nastic-segona-divisio/494392.html|title=\"Estic preparat per jugar amb el N\u00e0stic a la Segona Divisi\u00f3 A\"|trans-title=\"I am prepared to play for ''N\u00e0stic'' in Segunda Divisi\u00f3n\"|publisher=Regi\u00f3 7|language=ca|date=27 August 2018|access-date=8 October 2018}}</ref> On 10 July 2017, he signed a two-year contract with [[Gimn\u00e0stic de Tarragona]], being assigned to [[CF Pobla de Mafumet|the farm team]] in [[Tercera Divisi\u00f3n]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.elvallenc.cat/esports/la-pobla-anuncia-tres-fitxatges-i-puja-vuit-juvenils/|title=La Pobla anuncia tres fitxatges i puja vuit juvenils|trans-title=Pobla announce three signings and promote eight ''juvenils''|publisher=El Vallenc|language=ca|date=10 July 2017|access-date=8 October 2018}}</ref>\n\nFerrer made his debut for Pobla on 17 September 2017, coming on as a second-half [[Substitute (association football)|substitute]] for [[Pol Valent\u00edn]] in a 1\u20130 home win against [[FC Vilafranca]]. He scored his first goal the following 22 April, netting the game's only in an away defeat of [[FC Santboi\u00e0]].\n\nFerrer made his professional debut on 7 October 2018, replacing [[Roger Figueras]] in a 1\u20131 away draw against [[C\u00e1diz CF]] for the [[Segunda Divisi\u00f3n]] championship.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.marca.com/futbol/segunda-division/cronica/2018/10/07/5bba64f9ca474167308b45f2.html|title=Un inseguro C\u00e1diz tropieza otra vez en Carranza|trans-title=An insecure C\u00e1diz slip again at the Carranza|publisher=[[Marca (newspaper)|Marca]]|language=es|date=7 October 2018|access-date=8 October 2018}}</ref> The following 21 January, after establishing himself as a starter under [[Enrique Mart\u00edn]], he renewed his contract until 2021.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gimnasticdetarragona.cat/salva-ferrer-grana-fins-al-2021/|title=Salva Ferrer, grana fins al 2021|trans-title=Salva Ferrer, ''grana'' until 2021|publisher=Gimn\u00e0stic Tarragona|language=ca|date=21 January 2019|accessdate=26 January 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn 9 August 2019, Ferrer was transferred to Italian [[Serie B]] side [[Spezia Calcio]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gimnasticdetarragona.cat/noticia/20190809140830|title=Salva Ferrer marxa traspassat a l'Spezia|trans-title=Salva Ferrer is transferred to Spezia|publisher=Gimn\u00e0stic Tarragona|language=ca|date=9 August 2019|accessdate=12 August 2019}}</ref> and signed a four-year deal with the club.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{BDFutbol|21873}}\n*{{LaPreferente|232858<!-- /salva -->}}\n*{{Soccerway|salvador-ferrer/575287}}\n\n{{Spezia Calcio squad}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ferrer, Salva}}\n[[Category:1998 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Baix Llobregat]]\n[[Category:Spanish footballers]]\n[[Category:Catalan footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football defenders]]\n[[Category:Segunda Divisi\u00f3n players]]\n[[Category:Tercera Divisi\u00f3n players]]\n[[Category:CF Damm players]]\n[[Category:CF Pobla de Mafumet footballers]]\n[[Category:Gimn\u00e0stic de Tarragona footballers]]\n[[Category:Spezia Calcio players]]\n[[Category:Spanish expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Spanish expatriate sportspeople in Italy]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Italy]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Spanish footballer}}\n{{Spanish name|Ferrer|Canals}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Salva Ferrer\n| image =\n| caption = Salva Ferrer in 2018\n| fullname = Salvador Ferrer Canals\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1998|1|21|df=y}}\n| birth_place = Sant Joan Samora, Spain\n| height = 1.84 m\n| position = [[Defender (association football)#Centre-back|Centre back]]\n| currentclub = [[Spezia Calcio|Spezia]]\n| clubnumber = 21\n| youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = [[RCD Espanyol|Espanyol]]\n| youthyears2 = | youthclubs2 = J\u00e0bac Terrassa\n| youthyears3 = | youthclubs3 = Martorell\n| youthyears4 = 2016\u20132017 | youthclubs4 = [[CF Damm|Damm]]\n| years1 = 2015\u20132016 | clubs1 = Martorell | caps1 = | goals1 = \n| years2 = 2017\u20132018 | clubs2 = [[CF Pobla de Mafumet|Pobla Mafumet]] | caps2 = 41 | goals2 = 2\n| years3 = 2018\u20132019 | clubs3 = [[Gimn\u00e0stic de Tarragona|Gimn\u00e0stic]] | caps3 = 21 | goals3 = 0\n| years4 = 2019\u2013 | clubs4 = [[Spezia Calcio|Spezia]] | caps4 = 0 | goals4 = 0\n| nationalyears1 = | nationalteam1 = | nationalcaps1 = | nationalgoals1 = \n| club-update = 9 June 2019\n| nationalteam-update = \n}}\n'''Salvador''' \"'''Salva'''\" '''Ferrer Canals''' (born 21 January 1998) is a Spanish professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays for Italian club [[Spezia Calcio]] as a [[Defender (association football)#Centre-back|central defender]].\n\n==Club career==\nBorn in Sant Joan Samora, [[Province of Barcelona|Barcelona]], [[Catalonia]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gimnasticdetarragona.cat/jugador/salva|title=Salva|publisher=Gimn\u00e0stic Tarragona|language=ca|accessdate=11 June 2019}}</ref> Ferrer represented [[RCD Espanyol]], UFB J\u00e0bac Terrassa, CF Martorell \u2013 where he made his senior debut in ''Tercera Catalana''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://cfmartorell.cat/2018/08/27/la-perla-salva-ferrer-recorda-el-seu-passat-al-cf-martorell/|title='La perla' Salva Ferrer recorda el seu passat al CF Martorell|trans-title='The pearl' Salva Ferrer remembers his past at CF Martorell|publisher=CF Martorell|language=ca|date=27 August 2018|access-date=8 October 2018}}</ref> \u2013 and [[CF Damm]] as a youth.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.regio7.cat/esports/2018/08/27/preparat-jugar-nastic-segona-divisio/494392.html|title=\u00abEstic preparat per jugar amb el N\u00e0stic a la Segona Divisi\u00f3 A\u00bb|trans-title=\"I am prepared to play for ''N\u00e0stic'' in Segunda Divisi\u00f3n\"|publisher=Regi\u00f3 7|language=ca|date=27 August 2018|access-date=8 October 2018}}</ref> On 10 July 2017, he signed a two-year contract with [[Gimn\u00e0stic de Tarragona]], being assigned to [[CF Pobla de Mafumet|the farm team]] in [[Tercera Divisi\u00f3n]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.elvallenc.cat/esports/la-pobla-anuncia-tres-fitxatges-i-puja-vuit-juvenils/|title=La Pobla anuncia tres fitxatges i puja vuit juvenils|trans-title=Pobla announce three signings and promote eight ''juvenils''|publisher=El Vallenc|language=ca|date=10 July 2017|access-date=8 October 2018}}</ref>\n\nFerrer made his debut for Pobla on 17 September 2017, coming on as a second-half [[Substitute (association football)|substitute]] for [[Pol Valent\u00edn]] in a 1\u20130 home win against [[FC Vilafranca]]. He scored his first goal the following 22 April, netting the game's only in an away defeat of [[FC Santboi\u00e0]].\n\nFerrer made his professional debut on 7 October 2018, replacing [[Roger Figueras]] in a 1\u20131 away draw against [[C\u00e1diz CF]] for the [[Segunda Divisi\u00f3n]] championship.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.marca.com/futbol/segunda-division/cronica/2018/10/07/5bba64f9ca474167308b45f2.html|title=Un inseguro C\u00e1diz tropieza otra vez en Carranza|trans-title=An insecure C\u00e1diz slip again at the Carranza|publisher=[[Marca (newspaper)|Marca]]|language=es|date=7 October 2018|access-date=8 October 2018}}</ref> The following 21 January, after establishing himself as a starter under [[Enrique Mart\u00edn]], he renewed his contract until 2021.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gimnasticdetarragona.cat/salva-ferrer-grana-fins-al-2021/|title=Salva Ferrer, grana fins al 2021|trans-title=Salva Ferrer, ''grana'' until 2021|publisher=Gimn\u00e0stic Tarragona|language=ca|date=21 January 2019|accessdate=26 January 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn 9 August 2019, Ferrer was transferred to Italian [[Serie B]] side [[Spezia Calcio]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gimnasticdetarragona.cat/noticia/20190809140830|title=Salva Ferrer marxa traspassat a l'Spezia|trans-title=Salva Ferrer is transferred to Spezia|publisher=Gimn\u00e0stic Tarragona|language=ca|date=9 August 2019|accessdate=12 August 2019}}</ref> and signed a four-year deal with the club.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{BDFutbol|21873}}\n*{{LaPreferente|232858/salva}}\n*{{Soccerway|salvador-ferrer/575287}}\n\n{{Spezia Calcio squad}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ferrer, Salva}}\n[[Category:1998 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Baix Llobregat]]\n[[Category:Spanish footballers]]\n[[Category:Catalan footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football defenders]]\n[[Category:Segunda Divisi\u00f3n players]]\n[[Category:Tercera Divisi\u00f3n players]]\n[[Category:CF Damm players]]\n[[Category:CF Pobla de Mafumet footballers]]\n[[Category:Gimn\u00e0stic de Tarragona footballers]]\n[[Category:Spezia Calcio players]]\n[[Category:Spanish expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Spanish expatriate sportspeople in Italy]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Italy]]\n", "name_user": "Zyxw", "label": "safe", "comment": "update links, misc formatting", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Salva_Ferrer"}
